com.apw.carcontrol

Interface CarControl

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TrakSimControl

    public interface CarControl
    Wraps control of the car through either TrakSim or real-world car control.

    • Method Detail

      • readCameraImage

        byte[] readCameraImage()
        Gets the current image, from either FlyCamera or SimCamera. Also invalidates the current version of the processed/rendering images.
        Returns:
        The image as a Bayer-8 encoded byte array.

      • getRecentCameraImage

        byte[] getRecentCameraImage()
        Gets the most recent camera image as loaded from readCameraImage.
        Returns:
        The most recent camera image as a Bayer-8 encoded byte array.

      • getProcessedImage

        byte[] getProcessedImage()
        Gets a processed image. This should be processed and set through setCameraImage. If not, an exception may be thrown.
        Returns:
        The processed image in the form of a simple color raster array.

      • setProcessedImage

        void setProcessedImage(byte[] image)
        Sets the processed image.
        Parameters:
        image - The processed image in the form of a simple color raster array.

      • getRGBImage

        int[] getRGBImage()

      • setRenderedImage

        void setRenderedImage(int[] renderedImage)
        Sets the image to be rendered on the screen. Note that this will do nothing if there is no screen/window to draw on (willPaint returns false).
        Parameters:
        renderedImage - The image to render on the screen as an RGB integer array.

      • willPaint

        boolean willPaint()
        Checks if this car control will paint (if there is a screen/window to draw on).
        Returns:
        Whether or not the car control will paint.

      • exit

        void exit(int why)
        Closes open resources and exits.
        Parameters:
        why - Error code.

      • accelerate

        void accelerate(boolean absolute,
                int velocity)
        Accelerates the car.
        Parameters:
        absolute - If true, sets the velocity to the parameter given, else increments it by the parameter given.
        velocity - The velocity to set the car's velocity to or increment it by.

      • steer

        void steer(boolean absolute,
           int angle)
        Steers the car.
        Parameters:
        absolute - If true, sets the angle to the parameter given, else increments it by the parameter given.
        angle - The angle to set the car's angle to or increment it by.

      • manualSpeedControl

        void manualSpeedControl(boolean absolute,
                        int manualSpeed)
        Manually controls the speed of the car.
        Parameters:
        absolute - If true, sets the manual speed to the parameter given, else increments it by the parameter given.
        manualSpeed - The manual speed to set the car's velocity to or increment it by.

      • getEdges

        java.awt.Insets getEdges()

      • setEdges

        void setEdges(java.awt.Insets edges)
        Set the edges of the screen. If one does not exist, does nothing.
        Parameters:
        edges - The edges of the rendering window as a Java AWT Insets object.

      • rectFill

        void rectFill(int colo,
              int rx,
              int cx,
              int rz,
              int c)
        Draws a rectangle on the screen (if one exists).
        Parameters:
        colo - The pixel color to fill that rectangle, = 0x00RRGGBB
        rx - The pixel row in one corner
        cx - The pixel column in the same corner
        rz - The pixel row in the other corner (inclusive)
        c - The pixel column there
        See Also:
        TrakSim.RectFill(int, int, int, int, int)

      • addKeyEvent

        void addKeyEvent(int keyCode,
                 java.lang.Runnable action)
        Registers a key event.
        Parameters:
        keyCode - The key that should be pressed to trigger the action.
        action - The action to trigger when the key is pressed.
